# Interactive Video Questions System

## Overview
The interactive video questions system allows teachers to add questions at specific timestamps in lesson videos. Videos automatically pause at these points and require students to answer before continuing - similar to EdPuzzle.

## Core Data Structures

### VideoQuestion Type
Located in [src/types/assignment.ts](mdc:src/types/assignment.ts):

```typescript
interface VideoQuestion {
  id: string
  timestamp: number // When to pause video (in seconds)
  question: Question // Any question type (MC, numerical, open-response, essay)
  answered?: boolean
  studentAnswer?: any
  score?: number
}

interface LessonVideo {
  id: string
  title: string
  youtubeId: string
  duration?: string
  description?: string
  timestamp?: number // For starting at specific time
  questions?: VideoQuestion[] // EdPuzzle-like embedded questions
}
```

## Teacher Interface Components

### VideoQuestionEditor
**File**: [src/components/admin/VideoQuestionEditor.tsx](mdc:src/components/admin/VideoQuestionEditor.tsx)

Features:
- **Visual Timeline** - Interactive gradient timeline showing video duration
- **Embedded Video Player** - YouTube player with scrubbing controls
- **Auto-Duration Detection** - Gets actual video length from YouTube API
- **Click-to-Add Questions** - Click "Add Question Here" button at any timestamp
- **Question Management** - Edit, delete, reorder questions
- **Full Question Builder** - Integrates with existing QuestionEditor component

Usage pattern:
```typescript
<VideoQuestionEditor
  videoId={video.id}
  videoTitle={video.title}
  youtubeId={video.youtubeId}
  videoDuration={video.duration}
  initialQuestions={video.questions || []}
  onSave={(questions) => handleSave(video.id, questions)}
  onClose={() => setEditingQuestionsId(null)}
/>
```

### Integration in LessonVideoManager
**File**: [src/components/admin/LessonVideoManager.tsx](mdc:src/components/admin/LessonVideoManager.tsx)

Teachers access the question editor by:
1. Clicking the purple AlertCircle icon (⚡) on any video
2. Visual timeline editor appears inline
3. Scrub video to find perfect moment
4. Click "Add Question Here" button
5. Use full question builder with AI tools
6. Save all questions to database

## Student Experience Components

### YouTubeEmbed with Question Detection
**File**: [src/components/lessons/StudentLessonViewer.tsx](mdc:src/components/lessons/StudentLessonViewer.tsx)

Features:
- **Time Checking** - Monitors video playback every 500ms
- **Auto-Pause** - Pauses video at question timestamps (±1 second window)
- **Question Modal** - Beautiful overlay with question
- **Instant Feedback** - For MC and numerical questions
- **Auto-Resume** - Continues video after correct answer
- **One-Time Display** - Questions only show once per session

Implementation pattern:
```typescript
// Load YouTube IFrame API
useEffect(() => {
  // Load API script
  // Initialize player with event handlers
}, [videoId])

// Check for questions while playing
const startTimeChecking = () => {
  timeCheckInterval.current = setInterval(() => {
    const currentTime = playerRef.current.getCurrentTime()
    
    const unansweredQuestion = questions.find(q => 
      !answeredQuestions.has(q.id) && 
      currentTime >= q.timestamp && 
      currentTime < q.timestamp + 1
    )

    if (unansweredQuestion) {
      playerRef.current.pauseVideo()
      setCurrentQuestion(unansweredQuestion)
    }
  }, 500)
}
```

