## YouTube Player API Integration

### CSP Configuration
**File**: [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts)

Required Content Security Policy directives:
```typescript
"frame-src 'self' https://accounts.google.com https://content.googleapis.com https://www.youtube.com https://www.youtube-nocookie.com"
"script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval' https://apis.google.com https://accounts.google.com https://www.youtube.com https://s.ytimg.com"
"img-src 'self' data: blob: ... https://i.ytimg.com https://img.youtube.com"
```

### Player Initialization Pattern
```typescript
// Load YouTube IFrame API
const tag = document.createElement('script')
tag.src = 'https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api'
document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0].parentNode?.insertBefore(tag, firstScriptTag)

// Initialize player when ready
window.onYouTubeIframeAPIReady = () => {
  playerRef.current = new window.YT.Player(containerDiv, {
    videoId: youtubeId,
    playerVars: {
      enablejsapi: 1,
      origin: window.location.origin
    },
    events: {
      onReady: (event) => {
        // Get actual duration
        const duration = event.target.getDuration()
        onDurationDetected(duration)
      },
      onStateChange: (event) => {
        // Detect video end (event.data === 0)
        // Detect playing (event.data === 1)
      }
    }
  })
}
```

### Safety Checks
Always check if methods exist before calling:
```typescript
if (playerRef.current && typeof playerRef.current.seekTo === 'function') {
  playerRef.current.seekTo(timestamp, true)
}
```

## Visual Timeline Implementation

### Timeline Component Features
- Gradient background (blue → purple → pink)
- Click anywhere to add question
- Numbered question markers showing points
- Hover tooltips with timestamp and type
- Red playhead showing current video position
- Auto-sorts questions by timestamp

### Scrubbing Controls
- Play/Pause button
- Skip back 5 seconds
- Skip forward 5 seconds
- Slider for frame-accurate scrubbing
- Real-time timestamp display (MM:SS / MM:SS)
- "Add Question Here" button at current time

## Question Flow

### Teacher Workflow
1. Navigate to lesson management
2. Click video icon on lesson
3. Click question icon on specific video
4. Video player loads with timeline
5. Scrub to find perfect moment
6. Click "Add Question Here"
7. Question editor appears with timestamp pre-filled
8. Create question using AI tools
9. Click "Save Question"
10. Repeat for additional questions
11. Click "Save All Questions" when done

### Student Workflow
1. Start watching lesson video
2. Video plays normally
3. Reaches question timestamp → auto-pauses
4. Modal appears: "Video Paused - Answer to continue"
5. Student answers question
6. Receives instant feedback
7. Clicks "Continue Video" after correct answer
8. Video resumes from same position
9. Process repeats for each question

## Best Practices

### Question Timing
- Add questions **after** key concepts are explained
- Space questions 2-3 minutes apart
- Don't overwhelm students with too many questions
- Recommended: 1 question per 2-3 minutes of video

### Question Types
- **Multiple Choice** - Conceptual understanding checks
- **Numerical** - Calculation practice  
- **Open Response** - Deep understanding with AI grading
- **Essay** - Extended explanations (manual grading)

### Points Allocation
- Quick checks (MC): 1-3 points
- Calculations (Numerical): 3-5 points
- Explanations (Open Response): 5-10 points

